onsulting tc engineering  construction ec government services gs nonstrategic business and other its solutions include engineering services mission and logistics support solutions technology licensing consulting procurement construction construction management program management operations maintenance and other support services to a customer base including domestic and foreign governments international and national oil and gas companies independent refiners petrochemical producers fertilizer producers and manufacturers as of december   it had offices around the world with operations in over  countries and served customers in over  countriestcthe companys tc business segment combines kbr technologies knowledgebased services and its three specialty consulting brands granherne energo and gva under a single customerfacing global business this segment provides licensed technologies and consulting services to the hydrocarbons value chain from wellhead to crude refining and through refining and petrochemicals to specialty chemicals production in addition to sharing many of the same customers these brands share the approach of continuous customer involvement to deliver an optimal solution to meet the customers objectives through early planning and scope definition advanced technologies and project lifecycle supportecthe companys ec business segment provides project and program delivery solution across the globe its solutions leverage its operational and technical excellence as a global provider of epc for onshore oil and gas liquefied natural gas lng gas to liquids gtl oil refining petrochemicals chemicals fertilizers offshore oil and gas shallowwater deepwater subsea floating solutions floating production unit fpu floating production storage and offshore fpso floating liquefied natural gas flng and floating storage and regasification unit fsru and maintenance services through the brown  root industrial services brandgsthe companys gs business segment provides lifecycle support solutions to defense space aviation and other programs and missions for government agencies in the united states the united kingdom and australia as program management integrator kbr covers the full spectrum of defense space aviation and other government programs and missions from research and development through systems engineering test and evaluation systems integration program management to operations support maintenance and field logisticsthe company competes with fluor corporation jacobs engineering aecom science applications international corporation booz allen hamilton amec foster wheeler chicago bridge and iron chiyoda corporation jgc corporation mcdermott international technipfmc and worleyparsons » full overview of kbr company address kbr inc  jefferson st ste houston   tx    p f  company web links home page officers  directors name compensation loren carroll  stuart bradie  mark sopp  gregory conlon  john derbyshire  » more officers  directors kbr inc news briefkbr wins lbed contract for ammonia plant revamp in russia jul   brief‍global government services business kbrwyle wins threeyear task order​ jul   briefkbrwyle to provide technical services for dod missile defense systems jul   briefkbr ‍estimates operating cash flows for  to range from  mln mln may   briefkbr signs joint venture agreement with biv builders may   » more kbr news related topics stocksstock screenerindustrialsconstruction  engineering